act</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Prime/Defs.html#Nat.Prime\">Nat.Prime</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">ℤ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ha</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#legendreSym\">legendreSym</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Or\">∨</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#legendreSym\">legendreSym</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">-<span class=\"fn\">1</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `p ∤ a`, then `legendreSym p a` is `1` or `-1`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#legendreSym.eq_one_or_neg_one","kind":"theorem","line":134,"name":"legendreSym.eq_one_or_neg_one","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.lean#L134-L137"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#legendreSym.eq_pow\"><span class=\"name\">legendreSym</span>.<span class=\"name\">eq_pow</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#Fact\">Fact</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Prime/Defs.html#Nat.Prime\">Nat.Prime</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">ℤ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#legendreSym\">legendreSym</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> (<span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"We have the congruence `legendreSym p a ≡ a ^ (p / 2) mod p`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#legendreSym.eq_pow","kind":"theorem","line":115,"name":"legendreSym.eq_pow","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.lean#L115-L132"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#legendreSym\"><span class=\"name\">legendreSym</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#Fact\">Fact</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Prime/Defs.html#Nat.Prime\">Nat.Prime</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">ℤ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">ℤ</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The Legendre symbol of `a : ℤ` and a prime `p`, `legendreSym p a`,\nis an integer defined as\n\n* `0` if `a` is `0` modulo `p`;\n* `1` if `a` is a nonzero square modulo `p`\n* `-1` otherwise.\n\nNote the order of the arguments! The advantage of the order chosen here is\nthat `legendreSym p` is a multiplicative function `ℤ → ℤ`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#legendreSym","kind":"def","line":99,"name":"legendreSym","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.lean#L99-L110"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#ZMod.pow_div_two_eq_neg_one_or_one\"><span class=\"name\">ZMod</span>.<span class=\"name\">pow_div_two_eq_neg_one_or_one</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#Fact\">Fact</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Prime/Defs.html#Nat.Prime\">Nat.Prime</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ZMod/Defs.html#ZMod\">ZMod</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ha</span> : <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> (<span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Or\">∨</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> (<span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">-<span class=\"fn\">1</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `a : ZMod p` is nonzero, then `a^(p/2)` is either `1` or `-1`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#ZMod.pow_div_two_eq_neg_one_or_one","kind":"theorem","line":74,"name":"ZMod.pow_div_two_eq_neg_one_or_one","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.lean#L74-L82"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#ZMod.euler_criterion\"><span class=\"name\">ZMod</span>.<span class=\"name\">euler_criterion</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#Fact\">Fact</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Prime/Defs.html#Nat.Prime\">Nat.Prime</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ZMod/Defs.html#ZMod\">ZMod</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ha</span> : <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Even.html#IsSquare\">IsSquare</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> (<span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Euler's Criterion: a nonzero `a : ZMod p` is a square if and only if `x ^ (p / 2) = 1`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#ZMod.euler_criterion","kind":"theorem","line":61,"name":"ZMod.euler_criterion","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.lean#L61-L71"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#ZMod.euler_criterion_units\"><span class=\"name\">ZMod</span>.<span class=\"name\">euler_criterion_units</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#Fact\">Fact</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Prime/Defs.html#Nat.Prime\">Nat.Prime</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ZMod/Defs.html#ZMod\">ZMod</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span>)</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Units/Defs.html#Units\">ˣ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">(∃ (<span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ZMod/Defs.html#ZMod\">ZMod</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span>)</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Units/Defs.html#Units\">ˣ</a>), <span class=\"fn\">y</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> (<span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Euler's Criterion: A unit `x` of `ZMod p` is a square if and only if `x ^ (p / 2) = 1`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.html#ZMod.euler_criterion_units","kind":"theorem","line":49,"name":"ZMod.euler_criterion_units","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/Basic.lean#L49-L59"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.NumberTheory.LegendreSymbol.QuadraticChar.Basic"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.NumberTheory.LegendreSymbol.Basic"}